# .trivyignore — accepted/by-design trivy findings for the fleet (issue #114).
#
# Used by tests/security/trivy.sh (config lane). Every entry MUST be justified
# here. trivy keys ignores by the AVD id (the "AVD-DS-NNNN" / "AVD-KSV-NNNN"
# shown under each finding); the bare "DS-NNNN" in the report maps to it 1:1.
#
# Verify after edits:
#   tests/security/trivy.sh            # expect: clean, exit 0
#   trivy config containers --severity HIGH,CRITICAL   # eyeball what remains

# --- DS-0002  "Image user should not be 'root'"  (by design) ----------------
# Fires on ~all fleet Dockerfiles (no top-level `USER` line). This is the
# fleet's deliberate model, not an oversight:
#   - Benchmark/core/model/gateway images run the EVALUATION/test phase, which
#     ".agents/benchmarks/RULES.md:46" explicitly permits to run as root
#     ("Agent as non-root … The test phase MAY run as root").
#   - The agent — the one process that MUST be unprivileged
#     (".agents/agents/RULES.md:42") — is constrained at RUNTIME (compose/k8s
#     securityContext + the agent-nonroot audit), which a Dockerfile `USER`
#     line cannot express and trivy cannot see.
# A blanket "every image needs USER" is wrong for this fleet; hadolint's
# equivalent is likewise not enforced (.pre-commit-config.yaml). Runtime non-root
# is the real control and lives elsewhere.
AVD-DS-0002

# --- DS-0031  "Secrets passed via build-args/env"  (by design) --------------
# Fires twice on containers/core/benchmark-base-hf/Dockerfile: `ARG HF_TOKEN=""`
# and the `ENV HF_TOKEN=$HF_TOKEN` bridge. This is the sanctioned build-time
# secret pattern, not a leak:
#   - ".agents/RULES.md:86" (15.e): build-time secrets go through `args` with
#     empty defaults — `args = { HF_TOKEN = HF_TOKEN }`.
#   - The default is EMPTY; the production/CI path injects the value via
#     `--mount=type=secret,id=HF_TOKEN` (see the Dockerfile comment), so no
#     token is baked into image history. DS-0031 flags the *shape* (a secret-
#     named ARG/ENV), not a committed value.
#   - Leaked secret *values* are covered by gitleaks (verify step 22); this is a
#     different, complementary check, and the value here is intentionally absent.
AVD-DS-0031
